en_151107_0	President Maithripala Sirisena says that all should work together as one to push the country forward, toward a sustainable year, avoiding focus establishing absolute power.
en_151107_1	He was speaking at the inauguration of the Development vision for a sustainable era in 2030, sponsored by the UN.
en_151107_2	The inauguration was held at the Presidential Secretariat this morning.
en_151107_3	Speaking at the ceremony, Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe said that politicians could bear different opinions in the effort to pushing the country towards development.
en_151107_4	He said that all should unite to achieve the set development goals however.
en_151107_5	Speaker Karu Jayasuriya, Chief Justice K. Sripavan, several government ministers, provincial council chief ministers and public officials participated in the ceremony.
